c graph-reachability-v0 disconnected-no-path
c Variables r_{i,v} mean vertex v is reachable from s in at most i steps.
c Vertex order is s,a,b,t and depths are 0..3, so var = 4*i + vertex_index + 1.
c The graph has only undirected edges (s,a) and (b,t).  The final clause asserts
c r_{3,t}, contradicting the fixed-point reachability equations.
p cnf 16 41
